"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-07-27-Interview-with-Yang-Yang-China-s-first-Winter-Olympic-champion-1vzFgijy8Mw-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Copied  CGTN talked to China's first Winter Olympic champion Yang Yang. In 2002, she won gold at the Salt Lake City Games in the women's 500 meters in short track speed skating. Yang Yang holds an impressive collection of 59 world championship titles. And now she's working as a UNHCR Goodwill Ambassador and is the Vice President of the World Anti-Doping Agency. CGTN anchor Li Dongning talked to her before she heads to Paris to serve at the 2024 Games. Let us hear her stories of inspiration and her insights on sports' role.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"